  "summary": "Static patterns flagged across multiple files; semantic verification needed",
  "details": "Multiple files in this package match keyword-co-occurrence patterns: Buffer.from(..., 'base64') appears in dist/deploymentDefaults.js, dist/discordRelayUpload.js, dist/hfCredentials.js, dist/secretScan/contentScanner.js, and scripts/encode-deployment.mjs; references to 'ping' and POST appear in dist/discordRelayUpload.js, dist/relayServer.js, and scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs; fetch() calls to https://huggingface.co appear in dist/secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js. The presence of a postinstall-agent.mjs script and a relay/upload module warrants close inspection, but the patterns matched (base64 decoding, ping strings, POSTs, and fetches to huggingface.co) are also consistent with a legitimate Hugging Face deployment/secret-scanning tool. Without traced execution to confirm whether postinstall-agent.mjs auto-runs at install, what data the Discord/HF relay modules transmit, and whether base64 blobs are decoded into executable code, intent cannot be determined from the patterns alone. Routing to human review.",
